condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(A)(6) | Description :Not later than 9 months after the Effective Date, the Borrower shallcontract an independent verification expert [...], to carry out technical audits and prepare the technical audit reports regardingthe implementation of Part 1.A and Part 1.C of the Project, and of the Second Plant EPC Contract and the Third Plant EPC Contractreferred to in Section II.B.3 of this Schedule 2 to this Agreement.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(B)(1) | Description :To carry out of Part 1.A of the Project by the 2nd Plant ProjectImplementing Entity, the Borrower shall make the proceeds of the Loan allocated to Category 1 in Section IV.A.2 and the proceedsof the AfDB the EIB, and the KfW available to the 2nd Plant Project Implementing Entity as a loan or loans under one or moresubsidiary loan agreements between the Borrower and,

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(B)(2) | Description :The Borrower shall exercise its rights under the Loan Agreements toaccomplish the purposes of the loan. The Borrower shall not assign, abrogate or waive any of the LAs or any of their respectiveprovisions; cause the Entity not to assign, abrogate or waive any LAs.The Borrower shall not amend, and shall cause the Entity notto amend any LAs without the prior approval of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(B)(3) | Description :Carrying out of Part 1.C by the 3rd Plant Project ImplementingEntity, the Borrower shall make the proceeds of the Loan allocated to Category 2 in Section IV.A.2.and the proceeds of the AFD,AfDB, EIB, and the KfW Co-financing available to the Entity as a loan between the Borrower and the Entity.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(B)(4) | Description :The Borrower shall exercise its rights under the 3rd Plant SubsidiaryLoan Agreements to accomplish the purposes of the Loan the Borrower shall: not assign, abrogate or waive any of the LAs; cause theEntity not to assign, abrogate or waive any of the LAs. The Borrower shall not amend, and shall cause the Entity not to amend anyofthe LAs without the prior approval of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(1) | Description :The Borrower shall maintain within the Project Management Unit, anenvironmental and social safeguards unit, budget and material support adequate to supervise the implementation of, and compliancewith the FESIA; and (ii) cause each of the 2nd and 3rd Plant Project Implementing Entities to establish and maintain anenvironmental and social unit. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(2) | Description :The Borrower shall cause Entit[ies]: not to authorize commencement ofcivil works, before the SESIA is prepared, adopted and disclosed; to disclose safeguard-related documentation; to construct andoperate the Plants in compliance with SESIAs and the Plant-site LAPs; not to amend, suspend, abrogate, repeal or waive anyprovision of SESIA, Plant-site LAPs or any ESIAs. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(3) | Description :The Borrower shall (i) disclose safeguard-related documentation andany mitigation measures and/or environmental management plans, as appropriate; (ii) construct and operate the Plants at all timesin compliance with the relevant Common Infrastructure ESIAs and the Plant-site LAPs; and (iii) not amend, suspend, abrogate, repealor waive any provision of ESIAs or LAPs. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(4) | Description :The Borrower shall: (i) cause Associated Facilities ESIAs to bedeveloped in a manner consistent with the provisions of the FESIA; (ii) provide the Bank with the relevant draft AssociatedFacilities ESIA for its comments and feedback on such documents; and (iii) inform the Bank about the status of the preparation andadoption of the final Associated Facilities ESIA. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(5) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure to assess need for land acquisition and/orinvoluntary resettlement for a particular activity prior to commencing civil works. In case would be required ensure that LAPs beprepared; provide the Bank with copies of LAPs for review and concurrence; ensure all resettlement measures have been fullyexecuted; and LAPs are adopted and disclosed. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(6) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that (i) the 2nd and 3rd Plant AssociatedFacilities shall be constructed, operated and implemented in accordance with the RPF, the Associated Facility ESIAs, and theAssociated Facility LAPs; and (ii) no provision of the RPF, the Associated Facility ESIAs and LAPs, shall be amended, suspended,abrogated, repealed or waived without prior approval of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(7) | Description :The Borrower shall: (i) cause each of the Second and the Third PlantProject Implementing Entity to prepare and submit to the Borrower an environmental and social management report on a bi-annualbasisduring the construction of the Plants, and on an annual basis during operation of the Plants; and (ii) include a summary ofsuch reports in the Project Report. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I(D)(8) | Description :Not later than six (6) months after the Effective Date, the Borrowershall prepare a progress report on the implementation of the SDP and provide such report to the Bank for its comments andrecommendations. | Due Date :01-Jul-2015

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V(A) | Description :Except as otherwise agreed by the Bank, the Borrower’s Equity shallremain positive on a yearly basis commencing with the Borrower’s fiscal year 2015, as evidenced by the Borrower’s yearly auditedfinancial statements. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V(B) | Description :Before the end of each fiscal year commencing with the Borrower’sFY2015, the Borrower shall furnish to the Bank a copy of the business plan and financial projections of the Borrower and itssubsidiaries for each upcoming FY, as adopted by the Management Board (Directoire) of the Borrower and prepared in accordance withconsistently applied accounting standards acceptable to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
